@node "intro" "Introduction"

                                          - Introduction -
                                          

It all started off thx to rudeboy (rudeboy@d0td0t.demon.co.uk) who made this little program on the PC called "fader" (or something like that). This little program simply added a gradient fill to colours on HTML files.
 
I saw this little program, and I was quite impressed, so I decided that an Amiga port had to be made. I didn't know if there was another program like this on the Amiga (and still don't :).
 
Me and a friend (Gareth Williams) got together, and started to make some work on it. And it was pretty easy to make too, just took its time.
 
So here it is! HTMLGrad 1.0!!!!!
 
@endnode

