@node "shareware" "ShareWare"
 
This program is ShareWare. This means that the program is operational to a certain extent. There are several features disabled in the unregistered version. This is the only way we can encourage people to register HTMLGrad.
 
These are the disabled features:
 
 
        · External Text file converting disabled
        
        · Sentence string can only take 32 characters instead of 256
        
        · Pop-up requesters all over the place!
        

To get the full version please consider @{ "registering" link "register" 0}. We need the money!
 
@endnode

@node "features" "Features"

These are the features available on the demo version of HTMLGrad:
 
 
     · Sentence handling up to 32 characters
     
     · Left, Middle and Right colours available
     
     · Sexy "GO!" button :)
     
The fill package included the above features and the following:

     · Up to 256 characters in Sentence handling
     
     · External Text file converting (as many paragraphs as you like :)
     
     · No Annoyung pop-up requesters
     
@endnode      

@node "req" "System Requirements"

Unfortunately, this is the first release of HTMLGrad, so it hasn't really been tested extensively.

It has currently been tested under Workbench 3.0

You do however need the following requirements as a minimum

                · ReqTools.library
                
                · ASL.library
                
                · OS2.04 (If people could test it under this OS, please tell us!)
                
@endnode

@node "install" "Installing"

Simply click on the Install icon!

@endnode
 
@node "usage" "Usage"

Using HTMLGrad is easy PeeCee (ewwwww).
 
Simply click on the "Enter Sentence" string, and enter a little sentence. After that, go to the "Left Colour" RGB sliders. You will now have to select a colour for the beginning of the sentence. To do this, simply mix the colours. A sample colour will be shown on the box at the bottom.

Once you have selected the colour you want, simply go onto the next two (Middle Colour and Right Colour) and do the same as above. Once you have finished fiddling about with the colours, click on the "GO!" button and enter a filename. HTMLGrad will then save out the source code and you can view this with any browser (eg Voyager-NG, IBrowse, AWeb).

@endnode

